  "local_port": 44940,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some of the cool features on Google now?",
  "response": "Google Now, which has evolved into Google Assistant, offers a variety of useful features designed to make your life easier by providing information and services proactively. Here are some of the cool features you might enjoy:\n\n1. **Proactive Assistance**: Google Assistant anticipates your needs based on your habits, location, and preferences. For example, it can remind you to leave for the airport with a traffic estimate to ensure you arrive on time.\n\n2. **Voice Commands**: You can use voice commands to perform tasks such as setting alarms, sending messages, making phone calls, or even controlling smart home devices.\n\n3. **Routines**: You can set up routines that trigger multiple actions with a single command. For example, saying \"Good morning\" can turn on the lights, read the news, and give you the weather forecast.\n\n4. **Screen Call**: Google Assistant can answer calls for you, screen the caller, and provide you with a transcript of what\u2019s being said, so you can decide whether to pick up or call back.\n\n5. **Live Translation**: You can use Google Assistant to translate conversations in real-time. This can be incredibly handy when traveling or communicating with someone who speaks a different language.\n\n6. **Broadcast**: Send announcements to all Google Assistant devices in your home. This is perfect for calling everyone to dinner or alerting them about your arrival.\n\n7. **Interpreter Mode**: This feature allows for real-time translation between languages during a conversation, making it easier to communicate with people who speak different languages.\n\n8. **Personalized News Briefing**: Get a briefing tailored to your interests, including news, weather, and reminders.\n\n9. **Understanding Context**: Google Assistant can understand context over the course of a conversation, allowing for more natural interactions. For example, if you ask for the weather and then ask \"How about tomorrow?\", it knows you\u2019re asking for the next day\u2019s forecast.\n\n10. **Integration with Apps and Services**: Google Assistant works with a wide range of apps and services, allowing you to order food, book rides, play music, and more, all through voice commands.\n\n11. **Visual Snapshot**: It provides a visual overview of your day, including your schedule, reminders, and personalized information like stocks, weather, and news.\n\n12. **Voice Match**: It can recognize different voices and provide personalized responses based on who is speaking.\n\n13. **Control Smart Home Devices**: You can control a variety of smart home devices such as thermostats, security cameras, lights, and more, all through Google Assistant.\n\n14. **Find Your Phone**: If you\u2019ve misplaced your phone, you can use Google Assistant on another device to ring your phone, even if it\u2019s on silent.\n\n15. **Define and Explore**: Ask Google Assistant to define a word or provide detailed information on a topic of interest.\n\nThese features make Google Assistant a powerful tool for managing daily tasks and staying informed.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
